GOOD JOB TODAY.

139
00:12:06.183 --> 00:12:07.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
THIS IS NANA KOMATSU'S NUMBER

140
00:12:09.103 --> 00:12:13.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>If you don’t intend to see her,</i>
<i>I’ll take Nana for myself.</i>

141
00:12:28.622 --> 00:12:30.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ren!

142
00:12:38.757 --> 00:12:43.095 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, give me one too.

143
00:12:43.179 --> 00:12:44.138 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stop it.

144
00:12:45.431 --> 00:12:46.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, never mind.

145
00:12:47.308 --> 00:12:50.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can’t sleep, so I’m going
to Takumi’s room to play cards.

146
00:12:50.895 --> 00:12:51.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wanna come?

147
00:12:51.896 --> 00:12:53.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Cards again?

148
00:12:53.314 --> 00:12:55.774 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes. We’re playing Shichi Narabe again.

149
00:12:55.858 --> 00:12:58.611 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not the image of rock musicians, is it?

150
00:13:00.112 --> 00:13:02.072 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m fine. I’ll pass.

151
00:13:02.156 --> 00:13:03.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Being a rock musician and all.

152
00:13:04.033 --> 00:13:07.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let’s play! It’s no fun without you.

153
00:13:07.536 --> 00:13:10.831 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Takumi, Naoki and Take are
all lousy players.

154
00:13:10.915 --> 00:13:14.668 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s no fun winning all the games.

155
00:13:14.752 --> 00:13:19.590 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sorry, but I’m really tired.
I’m going to bed. Good night.

156
00:13:19.673 --> 00:13:22.551 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is that so? Darn.

157
00:13:23.969 --> 00:13:26.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Reira.
-Huh?

158
00:13:26.931 --> 00:13:29.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your voice is a bit rough. You okay?

159
00:13:31.477 --> 00:13:34.730 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let’s do our best, okay? Sixteen to go.

160
00:14:08.764 --> 00:14:10.641 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Who is it?
-Nana.

161
00:14:17.982 --> 00:14:22.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What a way to greet me.
You seem to be well.

162
00:14:25.197 --> 00:14:27.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I have something to talk to you about.</i>
<i>Can we meet now?</i>

163
00:14:30.286 --> 00:14:31.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sure.

164
00:14:31.453 --> 00:14:32.663 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Where are you now?</i>

165
00:14:33.289 --> 00:14:34.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In my hotel room.

166
00:14:34.582 --> 00:14:36.709 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-<i>Alone?</i>
-Yeah.

167
00:14:36.792 --> 00:14:38.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Would it be unwise for me to go there?</i>

168
00:14:38.919 --> 00:14:39.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No.

169
00:14:39.879 --> 00:14:41.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>If you’d rather meet me</i>
<i>outside somewhere, just tell me where.</i>

170
00:14:42.298 --> 00:14:44.174 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, that would be less convenient.

171
00:14:44.258 --> 00:14:46.385 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It doesn’t look like
I’ll be able to leave here.

172
00:14:46.468 --> 00:14:47.928 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Then I’m coming right now.</i>

173
00:14:48.679 --> 00:14:50.681 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What hotel and what’s the room number?

174
00:15:20.336 --> 00:15:22.421 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>So many fans…</i>

175
00:15:23.005 --> 00:15:24.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>They’ve found out</i>
<i>where the band’s staying.</i>

176
00:15:24.548 --> 00:15:25.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>No wonder he can’t go out.</i>

177
00:15:54.286 --> 00:15:57.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>What does Nana plan</i>
<i>to do once she meets Ren?</i>

178
00:15:58.624 --> 00:16:00.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>What’s she gonna tell him?</i>

179
00:16:01.877 --> 00:16:04.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Nana’s really stubborn, which worries me.</i>

180
00:16:05.589 --> 00:16:08.175 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I’m so worried that</i>
<i>it’s not likely I’ll get any sleep.</i>

181
00:16:29.488 --> 00:16:31.490 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good job.

182
00:16:32.116 --> 00:16:34.952 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you a staff member? Show me your pass.

183
00:16:35.995 --> 00:16:38.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, my pass?

184
00:16:38.205 --> 00:16:42.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It must be tough,
having to check passes here as well.

185
00:16:43.502 --> 00:16:48.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh? I think I left
it in my room. I’ll go get it.

186
00:16:48.215 --> 00:16:50.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This area is off limits to the public.

187
00:16:50.509 --> 00:16:52.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s a real problem.

188
00:16:52.511 --> 00:16:53.846 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you have any idea

189
00:16:53.929 --> 00:16:57.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
how much trouble obsessed fans
like you cause the band members?

190
00:16:57.891 --> 00:16:59.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I’m not really a fan!</i>

191
00:16:59.518 --> 00:17:01.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now go on. Go on home.

192
00:17:03.814 --> 00:17:05.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I asked that girl to come.

193
00:17:05.816 --> 00:17:08.610 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Please let her through. Here’s
a little payment to keep it a secret.

194
00:17:08.694 --> 00:17:11.071 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, is that so? Well, sorry about that.

195
00:17:31.592 --> 00:17:33.635 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The security’s really tight.

196
00:17:34.470 --> 00:17:36.805 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry, maybe I shouldn’t have come.

197
00:17:49.234 --> 00:17:50.152 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ren…

198
00:17:51.487 --> 00:17:52.488 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let me go!

199
00:17:52.571 --> 00:17:54.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have no intention
of getting back together with you!

200
00:17:54.615 --> 00:17:55.574 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wanted to see you.

201
00:18:11.381 --> 00:18:13.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I shouldn’t have come.</i>

202
00:18:23.977 --> 00:18:26.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re ingenious, Yasu.

203
00:18:27.064 --> 00:18:31.610 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Knowing Nana, naturally she’s gonna
feel the need to give the keys back to Ren

204
00:18:31.693 --> 00:18:33.153 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
after what you told her.

205
00:18:33.237 --> 00:18:34.071 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, I’ll take that! Pon.

206
00:18:34.154 --> 00:18:37.282 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But if she gives him the keys,
it would be over between them?

207
00:18:37.366 --> 00:18:39.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If she really wanted to end it with him,

208
00:18:39.201 --> 00:18:41.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
she wouldn't go through the trouble of
meeting him just to hand over some keys.

209
00:18:41.954 --> 00:18:44.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It just gives them an excuse to meet.

210
00:18:44.665 --> 00:18:47.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They’re man and woman.
Let that take care of the rest.

211
00:18:47.584 --> 00:18:51.088 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Shin, not that I care,
but you’ve been acting saucy lately.

212
00:18:51.171 --> 00:18:53.215 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don’t be so snobbish.

213
00:18:53.298 --> 00:18:54.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Oh, that’s Ron for me!
-Huh?

214
00:18:54.883 --> 00:18:57.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Did I win?
-He’s good.

215
00:18:57.636 --> 00:19:01.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You tricked me. You are so not cute.

216
00:19:01.640 --> 00:19:03.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mahjong is so much fun.

217
00:19:03.892 --> 00:19:05.519 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Next time,
we should play with four people.

218
00:19:05.602 --> 00:19:06.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Does Nana play too?

219
00:19:06.895 --> 00:19:09.314 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah. We used to play
a four-person game a lot

220
00:19:09.398 --> 00:19:10.774 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
when Ren was around.

221
00:19:10.858 --> 00:19:13.402 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Say, let’s ask Ren over next time.

222
00:19:13.485 --> 00:19:16.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really? I can meet Ren? I wanna see him!

223
00:19:16.488 --> 00:19:17.823 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wanna see him too!

224
00:19:17.906 --> 00:19:22.077 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why is it you're always
secretly meeting Ren behind my back?

225
00:19:22.161 --> 00:19:24.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m always left out.

226
00:19:24.246 --> 00:19:27.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Ren doesn’t have the guts to see you.
-Huh?

227
00:19:27.499 --> 00:19:31.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So he feels guilty about leaving BLAST.

228
00:19:32.212 --> 00:19:35.674 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He initially declined Trapnest’s offer,
you know.

229
00:19:36.800 --> 00:19:39.595 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then Takumi gave me a call.

230
00:19:39.678 --> 00:19:42.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was the one who persuaded Ren to join.

231
00:19:42.806 --> 00:19:46.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Still, he feels that he betrayed us.

232
00:19:47.978 --> 00:19:51.190 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There’s no need for him to fuss
over something that happened in the past.

233
00:19:51.273 --> 00:19:52.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It doesn’t suit him.

234
00:19:52.733 --> 00:19:55.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But that’s Ren for you.

235
00:19:55.611 --> 00:19:56.904 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can a guy so awkward with people

236
00:19:56.987 --> 00:19:59.615 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
really make it
in the brutal world of entertainment?

237
00:19:59.698 --> 00:20:01.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It worries me.

238
00:20:02.743 --> 00:20:06.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, in that case,
why don’t I send him an email?

239
00:20:06.538 --> 00:20:09.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-An invitation to a mahjong tournament.
-Yay!

240
00:20:09.249 --> 00:20:11.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He’ll be so happy that he’ll cry.

241
00:20:11.293 --> 00:20:15.547 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
By the way, Yasu,
you said you provoked Ren on the phone.

242
00:20:15.631 --> 00:20:16.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What did you say?

243
00:20:16.548 --> 00:20:20.344 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What tactics did you use?
Tell me so I can learn for myself.

244
00:20:20.427 --> 00:20:23.013 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don’t really have any tactics.

245
00:20:23.096 --> 00:20:24.932 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can’t you tell the level of my stupidity?

246
00:20:25.015 --> 00:20:28.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But you’re really smart! Unlike Nobu.

247
00:20:28.477 --> 00:20:30.562 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s not about how smart I am.

248
00:20:32.314 --> 00:20:34.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You still have a lot to learn.

249
00:20:42.699 --> 00:20:47.496 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Back then, I thought</i>
<i>I’d never wanna fall in love again.</i>

250
00:20:49.373 --> 00:20:54.044 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But that night, I wanted to dream again.</i>

251
00:20:54.711 --> 00:20:56.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I wanted to love someone</i>
<i>from the bottom of my heart,</i>

252
00:20:57.756 --> 00:21:00.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>no matter how I may get hurt,</i>
<i>no matter how I may suffer.</i>

253
00:21:01.176 --> 00:21:07.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That’s what I felt that night</i>
<i>while praying for your happiness, Nana.</i>

